From: https://developer.android.com/reference/android/database/sqlite/SQLiteDatabase.html#execSQL(java.lang.String)

&gt; public void execSQL(String sql) &lt;br/&gt; Execute a single SQL statement
&gt; that is NOT a SELECT or any other SQL statement that returns data.

So you could use this overload of `execSQL()` to insert or delete data but you would also have to concatenate the parameter that you want to pass with single quotes and this is not safe as it leaves your app wide open to [sql injection][1].&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Also from: https://developer.android.com/reference/android/database/sqlite/SQLiteDatabase.html#execSQL(java.lang.String,%20java.lang.Object%5B%5D)

&gt; public void execSQL(String sql, Object[] bindArgs) &lt;br/&gt;
&gt; Execute a single
&gt; SQL statement that is **NOT** a SELECT/INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE.&lt;br/&gt;

So [`execSQL()`][2] is **not** the recommended way to insert or delete rows.&lt;br/&gt;
Instead use the method [`insert()`][3] by supplying the column values in a `ContentValues` object and the method [`delete()`][4]:&lt;br/&gt;

    ContentValues cv = new ContentValues();
    cv.put(&quot;found&quot;, item.toString);
    boolean inserted = db.insert(&quot;list&quot;, null, cv) &gt; 0;
You can check the `boolean` variable `inserted` after this code to get if the insertion was successful.&lt;br/&gt;
And to delete the row:

    boolean deleted = db.delete(&quot;list&quot;, &quot;found = ?&quot;, new String[] {item.toString}) &gt; 0;

You can check the `boolean` variable `deleted` after this code to get if the deletion was successful.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
For this code to work you must have initialized the variable `db` properly and the name of the table must be `&quot;list&quot;` and the column&#39;s name `&quot;found&quot;`.&lt;br/&gt;
Also make sure that `item.toString()` returns the value that you want to search for.


  [1]: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SQL_injection
  [2]: https://developer.android.com/reference/android/database/sqlite/SQLiteDatabase.html#execSQL(java.lang.String,%20java.lang.Object%5B%5D)
  [3]: https://developer.android.com/reference/android/database/sqlite/SQLiteDatabase.html#insert(java.lang.String,%20java.lang.String,%20android.content.ContentValues)
  [4]: https://developer.android.com/reference/android/database/sqlite/SQLiteDatabase.html#delete(java.lang.String,%20java.lang.String,%20java.lang.String%5B%5D)

