I had the same error. I solved it by changing the the @ViewChild to a setter. This means whenever your paginator will be new initialized the datasource gets the new paginatior.
It&#180;s important to set the *static* propterty to false because it doesn&#180;t exist always.
```
@ViewChild(MatPaginator, {static: false}) set paginator(value: MatPaginator) {
    if(this.dataSource) {
      this.dataSource.paginator = value;
    }
}
```

This is happening because once the `schemaStatus` gets set to `false`, the `ViewChild` loses its reference to the `paginator` since `ngIf` removes the `paginator` from the DOM. We will need to set the paginator in the component again. You can use a setter in `ViewChild` to set your paginator but this would run in every change detection cycle. So instead you could force change detection using [`ChangeDetectorRef`][1] once you set `schemaStatus` back to `true`.
```js
import { ChangeDetectorRef } from &#39;@angular/core&#39;;
// Add other imports here

    constructor(private cd: ChangeDetectorRef) { }

    // Add this where you set schemaStatus to true
    this.schemaStatus = true;
    this.cd.detectChanges();
    this.dataSource.paginator = this.paginator;    
```

Here is a working [example][2].


  [1]: https://angular.io/api/core/ChangeDetectorRef
  [2]: https://stackblitz.com/edit/angular-mat-table-toggle-paginator

